<h2>Mount exFAT Filesystem</h2>



<p>The moment of truth! </p>



<p>While in the same <strong>/soft/sbin</strong> directory, let's run the <strong>mount.exfat-fuse</strong> command and attempt to mount the /dev/sdc1 filesystem again:</p>



<pre class="wp-block-preformatted">root@redhat:/soft/sbin # <strong>mkdir /exfat</strong> root@redhat:/soft/sbin # <strong>./mount.exfat-fuse /dev/sdc1 /exfat </strong>FUSE exfat 1.3.0 </pre>



<p>Success!</p>



<pre class="wp-block-preformatted">root@redhat:/soft/sbin # <strong>df -h /exfat</strong>
Filesystem      Size  Used Avail Use% Mounted on 
/dev/sdc1       932G  556G  377G  60% /exfat</pre>



<p>That's it! It's been fun <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/12.0.0-1/72x72/1f642.png" alt="ðŸ™‚" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></p>



<h2>See Also</h2>



