      <title>Quickly Finding files in macOS with mdfind</title>
      <link>http://tracking.feedpress.it/link/15217/12899995</link>
      <comments>https://www.unixtutorial.org/quickly-finding-files-in-macos-with-mdfind#disqus_thread</comments>
      <pubDate>Tue, 15 Oct 2019 22:54:53 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator><![CDATA[Gleb Reys]]></dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Mac OS]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.unixtutorial.org/?p=3502</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[macOS Mojave I've just learned about a super cool command in macOS: mdind. It consults a database to find files using type or filename. mdfind is quite similar to locate command, I think, but more powerful? Find file by filename with mdfind macOS comes with Apache webserver pre-installed &#8211; you just need to configure and [&#8230;]]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter"><img src="https://www.unixtutorial.org/images/MacOS-Mojave.png" alt="" class="wp-image-2122" srcset="https://34hkt337byg024dljl2cquwz-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/images/MacOS-Mojave.png 460w, https://34hkt337byg024dljl2cquwz-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/images/MacOS-Mojave-300x209.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 460px) 100vw, 460px" /><figcaption><strong>macOS Mojave</strong></figcaption></figure></div>



<p>I've just learned about a super cool command in <a href="/software/macos">macOS</a>: <strong>mdind</strong>. It consults a database to find files using type or filename. <strong>mdfind</strong> is quite similar to <a href="/commands/locate">locate command</a>, I think, but more powerful?</p>



<h2>Find file by filename with mdfind</h2>



<p><a href="/software/macos">macOS</a> comes with Apache webserver pre-installed &#8211; you just need to configure and active it. It starts with <strong>httpd.conf</strong> file, that is tricky to find unless you know where to look.</p>



<p><strong>mdfind</strong> instantly solves this challenge:</p>



<pre class="wp-block-preformatted">greys@maverick:~ $ <strong>mdfind -name httpd.conf</strong>
/private/etc/apache2/httpd.conf.pre-update
/private/etc/apache2/original/httpd.conf
/private/etc/apache2/httpd.conf</pre>



